==1968 season== {{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1968 |Team=Penn State Nittany Lions |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Independent |ShortConference= |Division= |CoachRank=3 |APRank=2 |Record=11â0 |ConfRecord= |HeadCoach=[[Joe Paterno]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |Captain=John Kulka |Captain2=[[Mike Reid (American football)|Mike Reid]] |Captain3=[[Steve Smear]] |OScheme= |DScheme= |Stadium=[[Beaver Stadium]] |Champion=[[Lambert-Meadowlands Trophy]] |BowlTourney=[[Orange Bowl (game)|Orange Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult=defeated [[Kansas Jayhawks football|Kansas]], 15â14 }}
The [[1968]] team was Paterno's first perfect season. Despite going 11â0, the Nittany Lions finished behind 9â0 [[Ohio State Buckeyes football|Ohio State]] and 9â0â1 [[University of Southern California Trojans football|USC]] in both polls.
