==1982 season== {{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1982 |Team=Penn State Nittany Lions |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Independent |ShortConference= |Division= |CoachRank=1 |APRank=1 |Record=11â1 |ConfRecord= |HeadCoach=[[Joe Paterno]] |OffCoach=[[Dick Anderson (American football coach)|Dick Anderson]] |DefCoach=[[Jerry Sandusky]] |OScheme= |DScheme= |Stadium=[[Beaver Stadium]] |Champion=[[NCAA Division I-A national football championship|National Champions]] |BowlTourney=[[Sugar Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult=defeated [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia]] }}
{{see also|1983 Sugar Bowl}}
Penn State defeated the [[Georgia Bulldogs football|Georgia Bulldogs]] 27â23 in the 1983 [[Sugar Bowl]] to win Paterno's first consensus [[NCAA Division I-A national football championship|national championship]].
