==1986 season== {{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1986 |Team=Penn State Nittany Lions |Image= |ImageSize= |Conference=Independent |ShortConference= |Division= |CoachRank=1 |APRank=1 |Record=12â0 |ConfRecord= |HeadCoach=[[Joe Paterno]] |OffCoach=Fran Ganter |DefCoach=[[Jerry Sandusky]] |OScheme= |DScheme= |Stadium=[[Beaver Stadium]] |Champion=[[NCAA Division I-A national football championship|National Champions]] |BowlTourney=[[Fiesta Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult=defeated [[Miami Hurricanes football|Miami]] }}
{{see also|1987 Fiesta Bowl}}
Penn State defeated the [[Miami Hurricanes football|Miami Hurricanes]] 14â10 in the [[1987 Fiesta Bowl]] to win Paterno's second consensus [[NCAA Division I-A national football championship|national championship]].
